{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/issues/22/comments/39810042.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/issues/22#comment-39810042"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/issues/22.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 22, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-common.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{1dfbdd30-34c5-4b09-82ef-9bfe2917877b}ts=1533303"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "ign-common", "full_name": "ignitionrobotics/ign-common", "uuid": "{1dfbdd30-34c5-4b09-82ef-9bfe2917877b}"}, "title": "GTSMeshUtils delaunay triangulation fails on OSX"}, "content": {"raw": "I think we based the code off this [delaunay.c](http://gerris.dalembert.upmc.fr/darcs/gts-stable/examples/delaunay.c) example. The difference here is new new `data` variable and the additional `Intersection` check. I'm wondering if something to do with packing `double`s and `int` into `gpointer` data and modifying the `int` in the `Intersection` function", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I think we based the code off this <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://gerris.dalembert.upmc.fr/darcs/gts-stable/examples/delaunay.c\" rel=\"nofollow\">delaunay.c</a> example. The difference here is new new <code>data</code> variable and the additional <code>Intersection</code> check. I'm wondering if something to do with packing <code>double</code>s and <code>int</code> into <code>gpointer</code> data and modifying the <code>int</code> in the <code>Intersection</code> function</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-09-12T19:40:40.251069+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ian Chen", "uuid": "{eaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Beaa